This is a potion that dulls the mind of the user so that he does not fear death or injury.
This thin liquid gives the consumer the ability to see concealed objects as if they were no longer invisible.
This potion grants the drinker the ability to walk softly and dampens sound around her slightly.
This vial contains a tiny amount of red liquid that feels warm to the touch.  When it is consumed, it allows the drinker to see objects in the dark as if it were day.
When consumed, this potion makes the drinker exceptionally lucky, giving him a better chance of succeeding at nearly everything he does.
A person drinking this potion gains an intuitive ability to hide.
Drinking this potion grants the imbiber the ability to notice acute details with great accuracy.

This bitter drink is brewed from beans brought from the continent of Maztica by Amnish explorers.  It is a stimulating tonic, though it can make one jittery as well.

Its rarity makes the price somewhat high.

Potions store various spells, both beneficial and otherwise, until consumed. This potion cures light wounds.

Under a detect magic cantrip or similar ability, it radiates an aura of faint conjuration.
When thrown, this item will burst open, creating a spectacle of sight and sound that is sure to baffle and frighten those who don't realize it's just a harmless illusion.
When these beads strike a hard surface, they ignite with a bright flash, dazzling all within the blast radius.
This luminescent dust clings to surfaces and creatures, making them glow.  The particles don't provide illumination, but are highly noticeable and prevent creatures from hiding themselves.

This is a healing kit, used to stop the bleeding and stabilize patients; provide long term care; and treat disease and poison.  Use of this kit confers a +2 healing bonus.

The kit is full of herbs, salves, bandages, and other useful material.  It may be used to stop bleeding, cure poison or disease, and increase the recovery rate of resting patients.  Use of this medicine bag confers a +2 healing bonus.
These bandages may be used to provide first aid or long-term care.  They do not treat poison or disease.

The handaxe is smaller than most axes used for combat, and is most often used as an off-hand weapon. 

This particular handaxe is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The battleaxe consists of a single blade atop a three- or four-foot shaft. It is a versatile weapon, and remains a useful tool when not in combat.

This particular battleaxe is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

Originally adapted from the tools of laborers and craftsmen, the warhammer is a far-heavier variant of the sledge and is no longer suitable for anything but combat.

This particular warhammer is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The light hammer is derived from commonly used mining tools. It remains small enough to still be used in excavation, unlike the much heavier warhammer. 

This particular light hammer is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The mace is a derivative of the basic club, consisting of a stone or metal head mounted on the end of a wooden shaft. The weight of the head greatly increases the force of impact.

This particular mace is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The morningstar is a derivative of the mace that includes a chain tether - similar to the flail - to add velocity when swinging its compact striking surface. Morningstars commonly have at least one formidable spike as an added feature of the head.

This particular morningstar is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

Derived from a farm implement used for threshing grain, the heavy flail consists of a four-foot wooden shaft attached to a heavy or spiked head by a chain or hinge. 

This particular heavy flail is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

Originally a farm implement for threshing grain, the light flail consists of a wooden shaft attached to a heavy or spiked head by a chain or hinge. The light flail is approximately two feet long.

This particular light flail is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type

The halberd is the most common polearm, and could be called a cross between a spear and an axe. Such weapons are often mass-produced for militia, and serve well when defending against marauders. 

This particular halberd is better balanced and better crafted than others of its type
